<!--321-->Under the Watching Eye x4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship--<br />
Big no more than 3, go first if you want. Get Aragorn and Gandalf out as fast as you can, and use Mr. Took on both, or on Gandalf if you get Aragorn out at Prancying Pony. Let Boromir and Gandalf and Aragorn take out all the big nasty nazgul, equipt with their weapons. Always try and stay a site or 2 ahead of the opponents, and make sure you play the sites(hopefully).<br />
<br />
Adventure--<br />
Moria Lake hurts me alittle, but not to bad. It hurts them even more, and plus its helps me out allllot. I picked Galadriel&#39;s Glade over Valley of the Silverlode because Valley lets them Frodo and them heal, which isn;t good.<br />
<br />
Shadow--<br />
Kill of everyone traveling with Frodo. Enquea takes them out, Scouting Band, Hunters, War Band, Hate, Under the Watching Eye. Make sure they assign Frodo with Thin and Stretched. Have fun, just kill them. Normally I kill off a companion by site 3 or 4, hopefully, then they just start popping away after that. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
